page.title: 10Jackdaw to the camp
page.content: We went on a trip from the Jackdaw Garage to the main gate at Honington.We saw at the garage some petrol pumps,some cars that needed repairing and a shop.On the other side of the road there was a corn field and beside that there was a bus stop.Further on there was a play school,church and some houses.Opposite the church was a grass field.Next to the grass field there was a little wood with a pond in it.We found out that almost all of the trees were deciduous. There was the HONINGTON CAMP POST OFFICE STORES and next to that there was a bus timetable.We found out that the bus goes from Bury St.Edmunds to Thetford and Thetford to Bury st.Edmunds.Then there were some more houses. Next to the houses was a barley field. Along its side there were sycamore trees.
